2026-03-12T06:00:05.034Z JOY-0058 comment.added "Analysis and solution plan:

Git is already used in joy init (repo detection) and joy assign (git config user.email). Reading git tags is consistent with this approach.

Data model:
- Add optional `version` field to Item (string, e.g. "v0.5.0")
- For bugs: version = "found in this version"
- On joy close: automatically set version to current git tag (latest reachable tag)
- New `fixed_in` not needed initially -- the version where an item was closed can be derived from the log

Commands:
- joy release [VERSION] -- show items closed since previous tag, grouped by type
- joy release (no arg) -- detect latest git tag automatically
- joy edit <ID> --version v0.5.0 -- manually set version
- joy ls --version v0.5.0 -- filter by version
- joy add bug "..." --version v0.5.0 -- set version on creation

Architecture:
- ADR for VCS abstraction: all git operations behind a trait in joy-core (e.g. VcsProvider) so other VCS can be supported later
- Consolidate existing git calls (init repo check, user email) into same abstraction
- If no git tags exist, skip automatic version detection silently -- no errors, no assumptions

Implementation todos:
- [ ] ADR for VCS abstraction
- [ ] Create VcsProvider trait in joy-core with git implementation
- [ ] Migrate existing git calls (init, assign) to VcsProvider
- [ ] Add version field to Item model
- [ ] Add --version flag to joy add, joy edit, joy ls
- [ ] Implement joy release command
- [ ] Update Vision.md and Tutorial.md" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
